A former presidential aide, Ahmed Gulak, has been shot dead in Imo State on Sunday.  Sources said that he was ambushed while on his way to Sam Mbakwe International Cargo airport. His motorcade was attacked at a place called Obiagwa, close to the Airport. The former aide to ex-president Goodluck Jonathan was attacked in his vehicle – Camry – marked Texas BFT 2150, The PUNCH was told. The state Commissioner of Police, Abutu Yaro, confirmed the development to The PUNCH. The CP said, “It is true but the details are sketchy. I am on the way to the airport. Please call the CP in charge of Airport. He will give more details. You know that Imo command is different from Airport command.” Details later…  Source By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Former Political Adviser to Dr Goodluck Jonathan and chieftain of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Mr Ahmed Gulak has alleged that the state governor, Rochas Okorocha offered him $2million to influence the outcome of the party’s primary in favour of his son-in-law, Uche… In "Top Stories" •Ndubuisi Emenike, shot by his security detail OWERRI -  Ndubuisi Emenike, the 2019 Imo North senatorial candidate of the Action Alliance (AA) is feared dead after being shot by his security detail, an operative of the Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps on Sunday (today).The incident took place around 5pm… In "Top Stories" Abuja (Sundiata Post) -  Suspected killers of Rev Fr.Jude Egbom of St Patrick’s Catholic church, Amucha, in the Njaba Local Government Area of the state have been arrested by the operatives of the Federal Special Anti-Robbery Squad of the Imo State police command.   Egbom was on Monday night along Nkwerre-Anara… In "Top Stories"